{"article_id":"uYtwoUeopcW13SIM","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"On Sunday evening , demonstrators","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"protesting the death of George Floyd","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"defaced and toppled a statue of Confederate officer Charles Linn ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"which had stood in a public park in Birmingham , Alabama ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"since being installed in 2013 by a charity .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The destruction of this Confederate monument is but one in a sequence of such vandalisms","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that have swept the nation ' s southern states in the past week .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"The Confederate Soldiers and Sailors Monument in Birmingham was defaced","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"before authorities disassembled","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"and relocated it .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"A Confederate monument on the University of Mississippi campus was vandalized Saturday evening by protesters .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"A statue of General Robert E. Lee in Richmond , Virginia , has likewise been a target of vandalism , along with Confederate statues in North and South Carolina .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"A 131-year-old statue of a Confederate soldier in Alexandria , Virginia , was removed","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"before any harm could come to it .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"In addition , a statue of Thomas Jefferson in Birmingham was set on fire ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"and a statue of Mayor Frank Rizzo of Philadelphia was graffitied .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"These latter figures ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"although not associated with the Confederacy ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"were vandalized for the same reason","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"-","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"their perceived racist attitudes and actions ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"called to attention in light of George Floyd ' s death .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Those","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"who would have memorials of the Confederacy removed","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"argue","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"that their presence causes civil unrest ,","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"while advocates of their staying put argue","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"that they are symbols of state heritage .","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"Protesters adamantly claim","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"that the statues ' removal will alleviate some racial tensions ;","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"others are skeptical","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"that the mere relocation of marble and bronze will solve any underlying social problems .","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"But what should be quite uncontroversial is that the deliberate destruction of public property is not an appropriate mode of protest ,","depth":3},{"id":33,"text":"besides being illegal .","depth":3},{"id":34,"text":"It isn ' t said nearly enough ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"but","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"by defacing and toppling Confederate statues ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"these protesters are doing a far worse injustice","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"than the states may have done","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"by erecting them .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"This country was built upon the Lockean idea","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"that property , both private and public , is sacred ,","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"and nothing","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"- not anger , not resentment , not unrest -","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"can justify its violation .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"To vandalize property is to scorn a sacred principle of the American system","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"and to reject one of the premises","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"upon which our nation was founded ,","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"and one of the reasons","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"why it has become so prosperous .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"In a republic ,","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"if citizens disagree with their government ' s actions ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"they are free to use their vote","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"to change the way","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"government makes its decisions .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"But one of the things","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"that enables a civil society to function","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"is that its citizens agree to submit to the state ' s judgment ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"even when they believe said judgment to be in error .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"It is this general agreement that keeps our civilization , even to this day , from descending once again into a Hobbesian nightmare .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"But","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"by vandalizing these statues ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"some protesters have shown","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"that they will not abide by the government ' s decisions","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"and are willing to break the law","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"to prove it .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"This spurning of the rule of law is toxic to the health of any republic","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"and ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"if it carries on unpunished","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"or is even encouraged by officials ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"will continue to grow","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"until bronze statues are not the only things","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"getting hurt .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"History is rife with examples of revolutions","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"that have disregarded basic rights to life and property .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"Such chaos has been commonplace since the French Revolution and the subsequent Reign of Terror .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"The events then and in many revolutions since serve as grim reminders","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"that no matter how righteous one ' s cause may be ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"going beyond the law","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"to address one ' s grievances","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"can easily upset a nation ' s social and political order","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"and lead to devastating and deadly unforeseen consequences .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"Whether in Birmingham or anywhere else , property , public and private , must be protected .","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"If these Confederate statues truly are stirring up the discord","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"accredited to them ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"then they should be removed in a manner","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"to be determined by law","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"- the citizens of any of these states are free to change their laws and their representatives .","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"And , if this is what citizens decide to do ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"then ,","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"regardless of whatever social value is lost or gained ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"there is nothing criminal in it .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"But the wanton defacement and destruction of public property","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"witnessed this week","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"is as inexcusable","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"as it is unlawful and unethical ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"and such vandalism must not be permitted to continue .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":193,"left":128,"right":192,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":128,"left":118,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":103,"right":117,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":101,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":98,"right":100,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":2,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"pare